nodes.title: About
widgets_values:
# Interfacial Workflow / Made by Project Soulstealer #

Interface: Ultimate Inkbunny Workflow
Version: v1.0.0 (composed of 3 different workflows - Variational Seed Generation v1.0.1 + Upscaler v1.0.1 + Variational Detail Enchancer v1.0.0)

This is the Ultimate All-In-One Workflow. It allows you to create anything, literally. However, it takes a lot of unnecessary actions in the process, and exists just for convinience of less experienced Neuroartists. So, how to use this workflow?

Step 1: Load checkpoint you wish to use, with config and clip. Apply all settings for model: CFG rescaler, CLIP SKIP, VAE, etc.
Step 2: Fill out parameters - Sampler steps, CFG, Width x Height, scheduler, sampler, and prompts.
Step 3: Set fixed seeds for initial noise and sampler.
Step 4: Press 'Queue Prompt' and wait till 16 variations will load up.
Step 5: Select IMAGE from sampler with variation that looks the best and connect it to First Upscaler node.
Step 6: Set seed for detailing (recommended to use same seed as used for generation) and CFG Rescale (recommended to try to use same as generation)
Step 6: Press 'Queue Prompt', and wait till another 16 images - now, upscaled variants - become available.
Step 7: Select best picture you have got and connect it's IMAGE to upscaler.
Step 8: Finally, press Queue Prompt last time.
Step 9: Save your upscaled image. Done!

Color Coding:
Cyan = Input nodes. You set information about what you want to those.
Yellow = Processing nodes. Don't touch those.
Green = Output nodes. This is where you get your result.
Black = Debug/Processing nodes. This is where you can see intermediate results.
